{
  "text": "Walking speed is assessed by asking the participants to walk at their usual pace over a 4 m course. Participants are instructed to stand with both feet touching the starting line and to start walking after a specific verbal command. Timing begins when the command is given, and the time needed to complete the entire distance is recorded. The faster of two walks is used. The reliability of the 4 m walk test is excellent e with an intraclass correlation coefficient (ICC) > 0.9 [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "27536821"
